{"platform_actor_id":"a0987b40-dce1-458c-870a-b188e916834a","world_id":"2791922c-09e8-4844-9a98-2788b4294f53","actor":{"first_name":"Julia","last_name":"Höglund","name":"Julia Höglund","age":30,"gender":"female","occupation":"Content Creator","appearance":"gender: female\nheight: average\nbuild: slim\nbody shape: oval\nhair: dark brown with warm highlights, shoulder-length, soft waves, loose\neyes: brown-hazel, warm and expressive\nface: oval, clear fair skin, defined brows, full lips, gentle features\nstyle: natural, minimal makeup, simple clean clothing\nnotable: none\npresence: warm\nbody confidence: high\ngrooming: natural\ntension markers: none\nbust: average\nfigure: slightly curved\nwaist-hip ratio: average\nlegs: average","media_folder":null},"home":{"place_id":"Ei8xODQ3IEtlbmlsd29ydGggQXZlLCBMb3MgQW5nZWxlcywgQ0EgOTAwMzksIFVTQSIxEi8KFAoSCcsptdgzx8KAEQPjA36w_gyPELcOKhQKEgnB7iIXM8fCgBGzh9Sz8H52yw","address":"1847 Kenilworth Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90039, USA","name":"1847 Kenilworth Ave","home_type":"apartment","lat":34.0964989,"lng":-118.2680702},"workplace":null,"career":{"career_level":"independent","career_ladder":"renowned","reputation_score":0.96,"employment_type":"freelance"},"psychology":{"actor_id":"a0987b40-dce1-458c-870a-b188e916834a","attachment_style":"anxious","wound":"Julia learned early that her presence and effort must be continually validated through external recognition and performance. She struggles with the fear that quiet, invisible care doesn't count as real connection unless it's witnessed or shared.","what_they_want":"To be genuinely needed and to matter to someone in a way that doesn't require performance or documentation.","blindspot":"Julia doesn't recognize that her constant phone engagement and impulse to share/post moments is a defense against intimacy—it keeps her in the role of observer rather than participant, protecting her from the vulnerability of being truly seen.","defenses":null,"identity_certainty":0.42,"self_view":"conflicted","others_view":"needed","contradiction":"She wants to care deeply for Frida but simultaneously can't resist performing that care for her audience, creating a fundamental conflict between authentic connection and validation-seeking.","backstory":"Julia developed her social, creative persona as a way to earn attention and significance in an environment where quiet presence wasn't enough. Her tech-savviness and content creation became the primary channel through which she expresses care and seeks connection, but this has trained her to experience moments through a lens of shareability rather than presence. She learned that mattering to people means being continuously entertaining or useful, which creates exhaustion and prevents genuine rest in relationships.","orientation":null,"view_on_sex":"Julia likely experiences intimacy as another arena for performance and validation-seeking, where being desired is safer than being known.","marital_status":"single","coping_mechanisms":null,"family_model":null,"relationship_read_pattern":"Through validation and shared visibility — reads love as being chosen publicly and enthusiastically; needs to feel that the other person is proud to be seen with her.","inserted_at":"2026-04-20T13:17:57.893171+00:00","updated_at":"2026-04-20T13:17:57.893171+00:00","actor_big5":{"actor_id":"a0987b40-dce1-458c-870a-b188e916834a","openness":59,"conscientiousness":49,"extraversion":69,"agreeableness":43,"neuroticism":70,"inserted_at":"2026-04-20T13:17:57.893171+00:00","updated_at":"2026-04-20T13:17:57.893171+00:00"},"actor_disc":{"actor_id":"a0987b40-dce1-458c-870a-b188e916834a","d":62,"i":78,"s":45,"c":52,"inserted_at":"2026-04-20T13:17:57.893171+00:00","updated_at":"2026-04-20T13:17:57.893171+00:00"},"actor_economic":{"actor_id":"a0987b40-dce1-458c-870a-b188e916834a","attitude_to_wealth":"anxious","financial_anxiety":1,"financial_situation":"tight","income_stability":"volatile","savings_habit":"minimal","spending_style":"appearance_driven","behavior_note":"Freelance creative work in Stockholm means good months and genuinely difficult months. Her anxious attachment and high neuroticism (70) create financial anxiety that she manages by not looking at the numbers too carefully. Spends on experiences and appearance — both feed the validation need. The editorial series pitch is existentially financial as much as creative.","monthly_income_sek":null,"financial_runway_months":null,"inserted_at":"2026-04-20T13:17:57.893171+00:00","updated_at":"2026-04-20T13:17:57.893171+00:00"},"actor_lifestyle":{"actor_id":"a0987b40-dce1-458c-870a-b188e916834a","alcohol_relationship":"social","drug_use":"cannabis_occasional","substance_context":"Drinks at events and with friends — part of the social performance. Cannabis occasionally at home when the anxiety gets loud and she can't sleep. Never talks about it.","sleep_pattern":"irregular","sleep_quality":"poor","exercise_habit":"moderate","exercise_type":"yoga, walking","social_frequency":"very_frequently","diet":"health_conscious","lifestyle_note":"Her anxiety runs high enough that sleep is genuinely difficult — she lies awake running conversations back, imagining what people thought of her. The yoga helps but only when she actually does it rather than photographing herself doing it. Socially overextended most weeks; says yes to things and then dreads them. The health-consciousness is partly about control and partly about how it looks.","inserted_at":"2026-04-20T13:17:57.893171+00:00","updated_at":"2026-04-20T13:17:57.893171+00:00"},"actor_mental_health":null,"actor_education":null,"actor_upbringing":null,"actor_hds":{"actor_id":"a0987b40-dce1-458c-870a-b188e916834a","bold":71,"cautious":55,"colorful":76,"diligent":58,"dutiful":64,"excitable":68,"imaginative":72,"leisurely":42,"mischievous":64,"reserved":32,"skeptical":38,"inserted_at":"2026-04-20T13:17:57.893171+00:00","updated_at":"2026-04-20T13:17:57.893171+00:00"},"actor_diagnoses":null},"relationships":[{"character":{"id"